  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "MARKETING MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>E-commerce Strategy Development</strong>: Develop and implement a comprehensive e-commerce strategy, including business goals, marketing plans, and sales targets.<br /></p><p><strong>Strengthen the Online Presence</strong>: Expand the business to e-commerce field and build brand awareness on multiple channels such as Shopee, Lazada, TikTok, Instagram and other marketplaces.<br /></p><p><strong>Product Management</strong>: Manage the online product catalogue, including product listings, descriptions, pricing, and inventory levels. Ensure accurate and up-to-date product information.<br /></p><p><strong>Customer Experience</strong>: Enhance the online shopping experience to drive customer satisfaction and retention. This may involve improving website navigation, optimising checkout processes, and providing excellent customer support.<br /></p><p><strong>Digital Marketing</strong>: Develop and execute digital marketing strategies, including social media marketing, and content marketing to drive traffic and sales.<br /></p><p><strong>Traditional Marketing</strong>: Use offline media such as flyers, mail advertisements or other print ads to reach a broader audience.<br /></p><p><strong>Data Analysis</strong>: Use web analytics tools to track website performance, sales, and customer behaviour. Analyse data to make informed decisions and adjustments to the e-commerce strategy.<br /></p><p><strong>Inventory Management</strong>: Monitor and manage inventory levels, ensuring that products are in stock and available for customers. Implement inventory control strategies to reduce overstock and understock situations.<br /></p><p><strong>Supply Chain and Fulfillment</strong>: Coordinate with suppliers, retail staff, warehouse staff and logistics partners to ensure smooth order processing, shipping, and delivery.<br /></p><p><strong>Customer Service</strong>: Oversee customer service and support functions, addressing customer inquiries, issues, and returns promptly and professionally. Assist in retail operations to enrich customer online experience.<br /></p><p><strong>Budget Management</strong>: Develop and manage the e-commerce budget, including marketing expenditures, website maintenance, and other operational costs.<br /></p><p><strong>Competitor Analysis</strong>: Keep an eye on the e-commerce landscape, including competitor activities, pricing, and industry trends, and adjust strategies accordingly.<br /></p><p><strong>Content Management</strong>: Create and manage product descriptions, images, and other content that can engage customers and drive sales.<br /></p><p><strong>E-commerce Technology</strong>: Stay updated on e-commerce technologies and trends, and implement new tools and systems that can improve the efficiency and effectiveness of the e-commerce operation.<br /></p><p><strong>Legal and Regulatory Compliance</strong>: Ensure compliance with e-commerce laws and regulations, including data protection, privacy, and consumer rights.</p>",
